narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Good grasp on high school level physics.
I learned more about physics and how to estimate certain values and information from movies. I learned about how to test if physics in movies are realistic based on the laws of physics.
Introductory physics and guesstimation
I understand the basics of physics way better now and it was an improved version of AP Physics back in high school
mainly just physics, but I also learned how to approximate, which I think will help with consulting type interview questions

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Practice material for the exams could be a little more helpful

Strengths = There are many resources and an organized website. There is a TF to help.
Weaknesses = For the homeworks, there was sometimes not enough time to reach out for help. The homework also required some information or application that we did not go over in class or the other lectures.
The professor taught SUPER well.
Way too much work; way too difficult to get a good score. I genuinely worked harder than I've worked in most other classes at Yale, and I got a C I think.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yea, but be prepared to do a lot of problem sets.

If someone is interested in learning about how to see if movies are realistic, and if someone is interested in applying physics to movies, then I do recommend this class. I also recommend this class if someone is well versed in physics.
Yes if you want to learn physics with a great professor!
I thought it was interesting but a bit too rigorous and hard for an "easy science" class.

comments: As a film major, I can now analyze films with the knowledge I learned about physics and see how the realism or lack thereof contributes to the effect of the movie.
Watching movies that involve action scene would be so much more fun now.
